12:44.371 --> 12:45.703
that I'd like to wear.

12:45.705 --> 12:46.571
Fine.

12:46.573 --> 12:47.905
Oh, no.

12:47.907 --> 12:50.491
Maybe I'll go put it on
right now.

12:50.493 --> 12:51.993
Go right ahead.
What?

12:51.995 --> 12:53.094
I'm so sorry.

12:53.096 --> 12:54.111
What, why?

12:54.113 --> 12:56.581
I know this story, too.

12:56.583 --> 12:57.268
Really?

12:57.293 --> 13:00.118
Mm-hmm. Yeah. Robin and Lily get
in a big fight

13:00.119 --> 13:02.837
and then, a few minutes later,
there's a knock at the door.

13:04.390 --> 13:06.507
Hello.

13:11.344 --> 13:12.936
I've told you
this one before.

13:12.961 --> 13:14.370
A few times.

13:14.371 --> 13:16.354
I'm just...

13:16.356 --> 13:19.874
a boring old man
who won't stop spinning yarns.

13:19.876 --> 13:22.894
Oh, hey. I love your yarns.

13:22.896 --> 13:25.780
I hope you never stop
spinning them.

13:26.648 --> 13:28.850
But...

13:28.852 --> 13:31.769
You're the love of my life,
Pooh Bear.

13:31.771 --> 13:33.955
I just worry about you.

13:33.957 --> 13:39.860
I don't want you to be the guy
who lives in his stories.

13:40.579 --> 13:43.664
Life only moves forward.

13:46.301 --> 13:48.302
So what happens next?

13:48.304 --> 13:50.521
With Lily and the wedding dress,
I mean.

13:50.523 --> 13:53.474
Well... she brought the dress

13:53.476 --> 13:56.060
so that she and Marshall could
get new wedding photos taken.

13:56.062 --> 13:59.614
Because in yet <i>another</i> story
that I know...

13:59.616 --> 14:02.216
No!

14:02.218 --> 14:05.153
What kind of space would I have
in my brain for other things

14:05.155 --> 14:06.988
if I didn't know all this?

14:07.740 --> 14:09.741
Eh, probably just state birds

14:09.743 --> 14:10.942
or some crap.

14:10.944 --> 14:12.894
So, uh,

14:12.896 --> 14:15.446
Lily wanted to borrow
Robin's photographer.

14:15.448 --> 14:18.399
That shouldn't be a problem.
Shouldn't be

14:18.401 --> 14:21.085
a problem, Robin? Of course
it should be a problem.

14:21.087 --> 14:22.503
This is your wedding.

14:22.505 --> 14:25.273
You can't let somebody borrow
your photographer.

14:25.275 --> 14:26.758
Don't worry.
She's not serious, Robin.

14:26.760 --> 14:29.260
I didn't even bring the suit
that I wore to our wedding.

14:29.262 --> 14:30.411
Yes, you did.

14:30.413 --> 14:31.262
It's in our room.

14:31.264 --> 14:32.464
Go put it on.
We're doing this.

14:32.465 --> 14:35.183
And, Robin,
since you don't seem to care,

14:35.185 --> 14:37.852
I think I'll be wearing this
to the ceremony.

14:37.854 --> 14:39.137
Fine!
Fine!

14:39.139 --> 14:41.773
Fine. There's a very simple
solution here.

14:41.775 --> 14:43.724
We might as well just face it.

14:45.695 --> 14:48.429
U.S. Marines have to get married
in uniform, so...

14:48.431 --> 14:50.198
I'll just go enlist.

14:50.200 --> 14:52.099
Dude,

14:52.101 --> 14:54.051
we can enlist together!
That's the dream!

14:54.053 --> 14:54.587
That's not the...

14:54.612 --> 14:56.636
I wonder if they let you
pick bunkmates. I hope they do.

14:56.637 --> 14:59.374
Although I might want to request
a single. You'll make friends.

14:59.375 --> 15:00.708
Look, enough of this.

15:00.710 --> 15:03.461
Tim made you this amazing suit.

15:03.463 --> 15:04.745
Put it on.

15:07.916 --> 15:10.051
This feels weird.

15:10.053 --> 15:11.369
That's because it's new.

15:11.371 --> 15:13.137
It's a suit that's never
been worn before,

15:13.139 --> 15:15.423
a suit you never dreamed
you'd wear.

15:15.425 --> 15:18.943
All of this suit's memories
are still ahead of it.

15:18.945 --> 15:20.611
Look,
picture it, huh?

15:20.613 --> 15:22.647
The ceremony.

15:22.649 --> 15:25.933
When everyone stands up for me?
They do that for her.

15:26.801 --> 15:28.402
They should.

15:28.404 --> 15:30.138
She's gonna
look amazing.

15:30.140 --> 15:31.506
You'd better
believe it.

15:31.508 --> 15:34.325
She walks
down the aisle,

15:34.327 --> 15:36.310
you say your vows,

15:36.312 --> 15:38.812
you go
to the reception,

15:38.814 --> 15:40.814
you have
your first dance.

15:40.816 --> 15:43.835
And before you know it,
just like magic,

15:43.837 --> 15:46.204
you realize...

15:46.206 --> 15:48.256
it's a perfect fit.

15:50.342 --> 15:52.326
You're right, Ted.

15:52.328 --> 15:54.495
This is the one.

15:55.881 --> 15:57.381
Thanks.

15:59.801 --> 16:01.452
So...

16:01.454 --> 16:04.055
belts.

16:07.726 --> 16:09.093
Hey, Lil. Nice dress.

16:09.095 --> 16:11.028
You two were made
for each other.

16:11.030 --> 16:13.681
Like, does no one care
that I'm wearing this dress?

16:13.683 --> 16:15.149
I care.

16:15.151 --> 16:16.951
Okay. Now you're good.

16:16.953 --> 16:18.569
Okay, look,

16:18.571 --> 16:21.656
I know this is your
wedding, but this is

16:21.658 --> 16:23.541
a big moment
for all of us.

16:23.543 --> 16:26.043
This may be the last time
we're all hanging out together

16:26.045 --> 16:28.062
for who knows how long.

16:28.064 --> 16:29.080
I mean, tomorrow
morning,

16:29.082 --> 16:30.381
Ted's leaving
for Chicag...

16:30.383 --> 16:33.885
Oh, boy.
Lily.

16:33.887 --> 16:36.254
Wait, you already know.

16:37.022 --> 16:38.523
You already know.

16:38.525 --> 16:40.341
You're married to
Lily, which means...

16:40.343 --> 16:42.159
She pocket-texted me
while you were telling her.

16:42.161 --> 16:44.178
So...

16:44.180 --> 16:47.047
everybody knows I'm moving
to Chicago tomorrow.

16:47.049 --> 16:49.734
Lily's right.

16:49.736 --> 16:52.954
We don't know the next time
that we'll all be together.

16:52.956 --> 16:55.273
<i>And then I think</i>
<i>it hit all of us.</i>

16:55.275 --> 16:57.325
<i>We didn't know the next time</i>
<i>we'd be together.</i>

16:57.327 --> 17:01.045
<i>This was it.</i>

17:01.047 --> 17:02.163
And it's funny.

17:02.165 --> 17:03.247
In a moment like that,

17:03.249 --> 17:04.231
when what's really happening

17:04.233 --> 17:06.083
is too intense to deal with,

17:06.085 --> 17:08.202
sometimes it's best...

17:09.771 --> 17:12.740
To leave it unspoken

17:12.742 --> 17:16.127
and just enjoy
each other's company instead.

17:17.628 --> 17:20.131
You know, I've been wanting
to see this movie.

17:20.133 --> 17:22.516
Yes, movie time.

17:22.518 --> 17:23.968
So it's not bad luck for the...

17:23.970 --> 17:26.542
bride to see the groom
in his wedding suit?

17:26.568 --> 17:27.021
No,

17:27.022 --> 17:28.839
I think it's fine. Nice tie.

17:28.841 --> 17:31.726
Thanks. There was a cornflower
blue one I almost went with.

17:31.728 --> 17:32.977
Oh. Um,

17:32.979 --> 17:34.812
that would've brought out
your eyes.

17:36.565 --> 17:38.265
You brought more than one tie,
right?

17:38.267 --> 17:40.334
I was trying to pack light.

17:40.336 --> 17:42.570
Hey, you know what, maybe the, uh,
groomsmen should go get some food.

17:42.572 --> 17:44.405
I don't want Ted to have
to sit through this movie.

17:44.407 --> 17:46.240
Ah. I appreciate that, Narshall.

17:46.242 --> 17:47.224
Really?

17:47.226 --> 17:50.044
Aw, damn it.
Sorry, I saw it on a plane.

17:50.046 --> 17:51.542
What, so this is gonna be,
like, a thing now?

17:51.567 --> 17:51.997
Yeah,

17:51.998 --> 17:54.949
it's gonna be a thing now,
Narshall. Right?

17:54.951 --> 17:56.550
Narshall.
 Dude,

17:56.552 --> 17:58.169
settle down, Swarley.

17:58.171 --> 17:59.503
Yeah.

17:59.505 --> 18:01.872
Yeah, Swarlize Theron,
take it easy.

18:01.874 --> 18:05.459
Man, this was supposed
to be my special day.

18:07.962 --> 18:11.482
Oh. Hey, we survived the storm!

18:11.484 --> 18:15.569
Oh, Narshall,
did you do that?

18:15.571 --> 18:17.571
Nope. Wasn't me.

18:17.573 --> 18:19.824
Well, then who was it?

18:23.663 --> 18:25.446
A gorilla! Gorilla!

18:25.448 --> 18:26.614
So that

18:26.616 --> 18:28.148
really happened to Ted?

18:28.150 --> 18:30.334
That is exactly
what went down.

18:30.336 --> 18:32.019
Chapter and verse.

18:32.021 --> 18:33.788
Uh-oh. Out of ice.

18:33.790 --> 18:36.490
I'll get it.
Oh, no. Got it. Sit down.

18:36.492 --> 18:38.158
Plus, the, uh, vending machine's
got a loose coil.

18:38.160 --> 18:39.627
I'm gonna try
to hip check my way

18:39.629 --> 18:41.212
into some free
Tropical Skittles.

18:44.550 --> 18:47.284
Your sister's not
like most brides, is she?

18:47.286 --> 18:50.504
She's a Scherbatsky.
She's not gonna lose her Timbits

18:50.506 --> 18:52.289
just 'cause she's getting
married.

18:53.859 --> 18:56.394
I guess some people
just never have that

18:56.396 --> 19:00.331
"holy crap,
this is my wedding" moment.

19:08.323 --> 19:09.640
Mom?

19:17.833 --> 19:20.200
<i>That's the story.</i>

19:20.202 --> 19:22.386
Right down
to the surprise ending.

19:22.388 --> 19:24.371
Is that really such a surprise?

19:24.373 --> 19:25.890
I mean, come on.

19:25.892 --> 19:27.374
Yeah, of course she showed up.

19:27.376 --> 19:30.544
What mother is gonna miss
her daughter's wedding?

19:36.234 --> 19:38.218
Oh, hey.

19:38.220 --> 19:41.605
No. Come on.

19:41.607 --> 19:43.858
It's okay. I'm fine.

19:43.860 --> 19:46.210
I'm okay.

19:49.165 --> 19:53.400
Did Barney really wear
a scuba suit into the bar?

19:53.402 --> 19:55.286
I've told you that story
a million times.

19:55.288 --> 19:57.171
Yeah, but where did Barney get
the scuba suit?

19:57.173 --> 20:00.074
He stole it.

20:00.076 --> 20:00.941
What?

20:00.943 --> 20:02.293
Yeah.

20:02.295 --> 20:03.677
I can't believe
I forgot that.

20:03.679 --> 20:05.880
He... walked right
into a sporting goods store,

20:05.882 --> 20:08.783
tried on a scuba suit,
and walked right out the door.

20:08.785 --> 20:11.352
Walked all the way home
in it, like, 20 blocks.

20:12.605 --> 20:13.854
Guy in a scuba suit,

20:13.856 --> 20:16.273
just walking down Broadway.
Ah.

20:16.275 --> 20:17.858
He should be in prison.

20:17.860 --> 20:20.644
Well, yeah, for lots of reasons.

20:20.646 --> 20:22.446
You know, the thief
of the group is Lily.

20:22.448 --> 20:24.315
Yes. Oh, my God. Lily...
No. She stole my heart.

20:24.317 --> 20:25.451
No, n-no, I'm telling you,
Lily, from like, uh...

20:25.476 --> 20:27.476
♪ She might be in Tangier

20:30.551 --> 20:35.304
♪ She left here
last early spring ♪

20:35.306 --> 20:42.311
♪ Is livin' there, I hear ♪

20:43.346 --> 20:47.316
♪ Say for me
that I'm all right ♪

20:47.318 --> 20:51.720
♪ Though things get
kind of slow ♪

20:51.722 --> 20:53.822
♪ She might think
that I've forgotten her ♪

20:53.824 --> 20:55.073
♪ Don't tell her it isn't so. ♪

